A template can choose content with `if`.

[codeblock, $code("bst"):
    [if signed_in:
        Welcome back
    [else]
        Please sign in
    ]
]

A template can repeat content with `loop`.

[codeblock, $code("bst"):
    [loop names |name|:
        <p>Hello [name]</p>
    ]
]

Two structural controls are available inside a template loop:

[codeblock, $code("text"):
    [break]
    [continue]
]

The first ends the loop. The second skips the rest of one iteration.

Template control flow builds output lazily at runtime unless a const template
requires it to finish during compilation.
